 easy; either call or use an internet cafe to make reservations. It\'s a cakewalk.In terms of flight reservations for your Oct. 6th return to London, LOADS of cheapie airlines fly to &amp; from London, so you really shouldn\'t have a huge problem. Unless you\'re certain you know where you\'ll be on October 5th, don\'t book a thing. Who knows you may be somewhere where you can take the train back.The fees for using debit cards vary- check with your bank. The conventional wisdom is to take out big chunks of money at a time, rather than smaller amounts every day or two (thus having the int\'l ATM fees be a smaller percentage of the whole amount). I wouldn\'t recommend cash advances on credit cards unless you\'re really stuck; the interest on cash advances is usually outrageously high, and you should only go that route if you\'ve lost your debit/ATM card and are waiting for your bank to send you a new one there in Europe.',0,'0','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)','',0,0),(192,214,'Park','polatin@careerleader.com','http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100003405721362','133.242.21.68','2012-04-04 22:01:44','2012-04-04 21:01:44','Hi guysI totally agree with you. First of all, I think to stay in a hseotl is for a short term only. But even if it’s cheaper, flat-shares are definitely more comfortable and definitely safer. When I spent 3 days in a hseotl in London, I just had to sleep in the same room of 20 people of my summer camp and it was quit difficult at the beginning but I can\'t tell really something about responsibilities. It was just strange because some people like me was tired and wanted to sleep however the other one didn\'t. So I think it\'s quit difficult to share the bed room with to many people and not only because of the hour but also because of the noise  Now I live in a flat-share since May, always in London but with 10 people from all the world. Actually I think to go in a flat-share is better because you can have your personal room, so you can such have more intimate and during the evening you can sleep in your room without to be disturb by the other people.Personally I like living in a flat-share because I have improved my English very fast and the people I have met here are really amazing. All of them are more than my family. I recommend a flat-share for students because it’s really more calm and so more easily to study than a hseotl.Dave',0,'0','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)','',0,0),(193,2025,'lekumtx','amvnac@zqkely.com','http://kqmgetyjlzcr.com/','91.201.64.4','2012-04-22 21:12:47','2012-04-22 20:12:47','UtDhOq  <a href=\"http://pifjazqrpztc.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">pifjazqrpztc</a>, [url=http://kjvhgfxhlpud.com/]kjvhgfxhlpud[/url], [link=http://esgiiprlmehv.com/]esgiiprlmehv[/link], http://yzukaepqsvoq.com/',0,'0','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)','',0,0),(194,1087,'wbqmvqjwyd','qpeddpwhvm@okmutj.com','http://www.ysmiwiwcmv.com/','146.0.73.233','2012-04-25 13:19:35','2012-04-25 12:19:35','zwxkmopgfftiptufmt, <a href=\"http://www.pojfczptru.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">dlspztpsgj</a> , [url=http://www.mqwrhjzpxc.com]shdoziojjw[/url], http://www.mtounsksos.com dlspztpsgj',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 GTB5','',0,0),(195,1087,'kiuxgrwpmm','nukcnhlzuh@jfucuw.com','http://www.piyrkpfvdh.com/','146.0.73.233','2012-04-26 00:52:52','2012-04-25 23:52:52','rtvrkopgfftiptufmt, <a href=\"http://www.suykngjhui.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">pwxvchjuha</a> , [url=http://www.kldndmapnn.com]cbzuusetqu[/url], http://www.fibvgkwpqc.com pwxvchjuha',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 GTB5','',0,0),(196,1087,'brjyfxvapf','abpoirmbyy@xpvxts.com','http://www.mlyctkaukc.com/','146.0.73.233','2012-04-26 17:18:19','2012-04-26 16:18:19','xffnwopgfftiptufmt, <a href=\"http://www.gqleztnqsi.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">ekawljkrlx</a> , [url=http://www.qlkyhins