ercat de la Boqueria before going to the park and find a picnic spot up there.\r\n\r\n<strong>To get there:</strong> Take the subway green line, L3, until the station De Lesseps. Follow the signs out of the subway, you will find signs along the road. Beware, the slope is steep to get to the park, but it\'s worth it. You can also take a cab... The opening hours of the park vary according to season, it is generally open from 10:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m., but closes later in summer. And remember, admission is free! You only need to pay if you want to visit the house of Gaudi.','Guell Park','Sumptuous mosaics adorn the Guell Park in many places. One of the best known is the salamander found near the entrance. At the top, from the terrace you have a beautiful view over the city and its various monuments.','publish','open','open','','guell-park','','\nhttp://www.aubergesdejeunesse.com/mercat-de-la-boqueria/','2010-06-26 00:25:06','2010-06-25 23:25:06','',0,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/?p=490',0,'post','',0),(1551,1,'2010-03-07 22:21:14','2010-03-07 22:21:14','<img src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/DSC05386-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Mercat de la Boqueria\" title=\"Mercat de la Boqueria\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-480\" />Ce marché dont les origines remontent au XIIIème siècle fait partie des incontournables de Barcelone. C\'est le marché le plus grand d\'Espagne, celui qui offre le plus de variété dans ses produits, et bien sûr le plus populaire parmi les touristes. Certains des marchands y sont installés depuis trois ou quatre générations!\r\n\r\nIl se trouve tout près de la Rambla, et sa structure métallique typique est facilement reconnaissable.\r\n\r\nPrenez le temps de vous promener à l\'intérieur au gré des allées, parmi les 300 et quelques marchands. Achetez-y des fruits, et pourquoi pas un peu de charcuterie et du pain pour préparer un pique-nique avant de partir en excursion au <a href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/parc-guell/\">parc Guell</a>. C\'est une alternative parfaite aux bars à tapas...\r\n\r\nAdresse: Plaça de la Boqueria, 08001 - Barcelona\r\nLe marché est ouvert du lundi au samedi de 8:00 à 20:30','Mercat de la Boqueria','Ce marché dont les origines remontent au XIIIème siècle fait partie des incontournables de Barcelone. C\'est le marché le plus grand d\'Espagne, celui qui offre le plus de variété dans ses produits, et bien sûr le plus populaire parmi les touristes. Certains des marchands y sont installés depuis trois ou quatre générations! ','inherit','open','open','','479-revision-10','','','2010-03-07 22:21:14','2010-03-07 22:21:14','',479,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/479-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1546,1,'2010-06-24 20:36:21','2010-06-24 19:36:21','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-491\" title=\"Parc Guell\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/DSC05422-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />World Heritage Site by UNESCO since 1984, the Parc Guell is one of the most visited places in the city. It is one of the major works of artist and architect Antonio Gaudi, who designed it in the early twentieth century, commissioned by his patron Eusebi Guell. He wanted to provide a park for the aristocracy of Barcelona, and actually, at the beginning of the project, the park was to be a city of  about sixty houses.\n\nSumptuous mosaics adorn the Park Guell in different places. One of the best known is the salamander found near the entrance. At the top, from the terrace is a beautiful view over the city and its various monuments.\n\nThe park is large, so allow enough time to visit. A half day would be ideal to browse all the aisles and take lots of pictures. You can also buy food at Mercat de la Boqueria before going and make a picnic on the spot.\n\n<strong>To get there:</strong>\nLe parc est grand, prévoyez donc assez de temps pour le visiter. Une demi-journée serait l\'idéal p