e holidays. It remains open until 10PM on Wednesdays and Fridays.\r\nAdmission is 9.50 euros, and you can get a ticket for 6 euros if you make your visit on Wednesday or Friday after 6PM. And remember that access to the museum is free the first Sunday of every month!\r\n\r\n<strong>Pour s\'y rendre</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Louvre Museum is located in the 1st arrondissement. It is accessible by subway, get off at the station Palais Royal - Musée du Louvre, served by lines 1 and 7. <a href=\"../batobus/\">Batobus</a> also provides access to the Louvre.\r\n\r\nAnd remember that if you want to stay in Paris in the area of the Louvre, we offer <a href=\"auberges/recherche/France/Paris\">a selection of hostels and guest houses</a>. Make your reservation online!','The Louvre museum','Le musée du Louvre est presque aussi emblématique de Paris que la Tour Eiffel. Plus grand musée de la ville et faisant partie des plus connus au monde (c\'est même le musée le plus visité au monde), Il offre à ses visiteurs une impressionnante collection d\'oeuvres d\'art.','inherit','open','open','','544-revision-8','','','2010-06-24 17:18:34','2010-06-24 16:18:34','',544,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/544-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1519,1,'2010-06-24 17:18:29','2010-06-24 16:18:29','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-585\" title=\"IMG_6999\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/IMG_6999-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Musée du Louvre à Paris, France\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />The Louvre is almost as emblematic of Paris as is the Eiffel Tower. Largest museum of the city and part of the world\'s best known (it is the most visited museum in the world), it offers its visitors an impressive collection of works of art. Its eight departments cover many periods of all backgrounds. This is a must on any visit to Paris.\n\nIt is at the Louvre that you should go if you want to get a close look at the Mona Lisa by Leonardo da Vinci. But you have to be patient, waiti