 d\'information (BPI) is open Monday to Friday (except Tuesday) from noon to 10PM and on weekends from 11AM to 10PM.\n\nRegarding admission fees, prices vary depending on what you want to see. It is possible to buy tickets in advance, online.\n\nThe Centre Pompidou in Paris is oneof the museums that are accessible through the Paris Museum Pass. This pass which is for enthusiasts of museums gives quick access to 60 museums and monuments in Paris and Ile de France for rates ranging from 32 € for 2 days at 64 € for 6 days.\n\nEt si vous voulez séjourner dans le quartier du Centre Pompidou, <a href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/auberges/recherche/France/Paris\">voyez notre sélection d\'auberges et petits hôtels</a> et faites votre réservation en ligne!','Centre Pompidou','','inherit','open','open','','555-revision-3','','','2010-06-24 17:42:39','2010-06-24 16:42:39','',555,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/555-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1521,1,'2010-06-24 17:39:22','2010-06-24 16:39:22','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-560\" title=\"pompidou2\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/pompidou2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Centre Georges Pompidou à Paris\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />The Centre Pompidou, also known as Beaubourg, was born in the 1970s under the leadership of President Georges Pompidou. Its architecture, which was the revolutionary,  is now part of the image of Paris.\n\nThe purpose of this space is to consolidate and make available various forms of public culture as contemporary art, music, graphic arts, design or books.\n\nThe Centre Pompidou also hosts one of the richest public libraries, according to the idea that President Pompidou had to attract visitors who would then have access to other cultural richness offered by the center. Many exhibitions are held regularly, do not forget to spend a few hours at Le centre Pompidou during your stay in Paris.\n<h3>To get there</h3>\nThe Pompidou Center is located in