ess.\n\nYou certainly will not get the chance to visit the Eiffel Tower in solitary : since its construction, and especially since the rise of international tourism, the number of visitors increased exponentially, and is fast approaching the milestone of 300 million visitors.\n<h3>Visits</h3>\nThe Eiffel Tower is open every day of the year from 9.30AM, closing hours vary by season. it closes at 0:45AM during summer and 11:45PM  the rest of the year. The stair closes earlier than the elevator, at 6:30PM.\n\nThe tariffs for accessing the second floor are € 8.10 per lift (€ 6.50 for people under 24 years old). If you\'re broke, you can always go on foot for 4.50 € (3.50 € for people under 24 years old).\nThe ticket to access the top by elevator is 13.10 € (11,50 € for prople under 24 years old).\nTo save time and avoid long lines, please buy your ticket online at the website of the Eiffel Tower!\n\nThe tours are free, but you can see behind the scenes of the Eiffel Tower in the company of a guide who will make you enter the original engine room. The visit lasts 1h30 and costs 20 € per person if you are 2.\n<h3>To get there</h3>\nThe Eiffel Tower is located on the Champs de Mars.  Several subway stations and commuter trains are nearby: The RER line C, lines 6, 8 and 9 subway.\nYou can also get there by Batobus, there is a pier nearby.','La Tour Eiffel','On peut facilement considérer la Tour Eiffel comme l’emblème de Paris. Qui ne la connaît pas ?\n\nConstruite par Gustave Eiffel en 1889, pour l’Exposition Universelle de Paris, elle était à l’époque le monument le plus haut du monde avec ses 300 mètres de hauteur. ','inherit','open','open','','530-revision-4','','','2010-06-24 18:48:46','2010-06-24 17:48:46','',530,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/530-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1530,1,'2010-06-24 18:43:53','2010-06-24 17:43:53','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-531\" title=\"toureiffel\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/0