, its entry price is 160 crowns. You can book a guided tour in French. Passionnés d’art nouveau? Ne manquez pas le Musée Mucha, au palais Kaunic baroque, dans le centre historique de Prague. L\'exposition principale de ce musée se concentre sur le travail et les oeuvres d\'Alphonse Mucha. Un documentaire de 30 minutes complète l\'exposition.\nAdresse: Kaunický palác, Panská 7, 110 00 Prague 1\nLe musée est ouvert tous les jours jusqu\'à 18h, son prix d\'entrée est de 160 couronnes. Vous pouvez réserver un tour guidé en français.','The Mucha museum','','inherit','open','open','','287-revision-3','','','2010-06-24 21:52:52','2010-06-24 20:52:52','',287,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/287-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1581,1,'2010-06-24 21:56:17','2010-06-24 20:56:17','If you have time, remember to take the funicular to reach the top of Petrin Hill, between orchards and woods. Beloved of the prople of Prague, it is  not only a good place to get some air and rest of the town, but it\'s also the perfect place to have a beautiful view of Prague.\r\nThe observatory tower on top of the hill, is a replica - smaller - of the Eiffel Tower in Paris.\r\nAccess: The funicular is taken at the tram station Ujezd (lines 12, 22, 23). You can also access the hill from the Strahov Monastery.\r\n\r\nIf you get hungry on the way down, stop at the excellent restaurant Nebozizek, mid-height on the hill. The food is excellent and the prices rather reasonable if one considers the extraordinary views of the city, which are included in the price!','Petrin Hill','','inherit','open','open','','285-revision-4','','','2010-06-24 21:56:17','2010-06-24 20:56:17','',285,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/285-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1580,1,'2010-06-24 21:55:48','2010-06-24 20:55:48','If you have time, remember to take the funicular to reach the top of Petrin Hill, between orchards and woods. Beloved of the prople of Prague, it is  not only a good place to get some air and rest of the town, but it\'s also the perfect place to have a beautiful view of Prague.\nThe observatory tower on top of the hill, is a replica - smaller - of the Eiffel Tower in Paris.\nAccess: The funicular is taken  the tram station Ujezd (lines 12, 22, 23). It can also access the hill from the Strahov Monastery.\n\nIf you get hungry on the way down, stop at the excellent restaurant Nebozizek, mid-height on the hill. The food is excellent and the prices rather reasonable if one considers the extraordinary views of the city, which is included in the price!\n\nSi vous en avez le temps, n’oubliez pas de prendre le funiculaire pour vous rendre au sommet de la colline de Petrin, entre vergers et bois. Très aimée des pragois, c\'est non seulement c’est un bon endroit pour prendre l’air et vous reposer de la ville, mais c’est aussi le lieu idéal pour avoir une superbe vue de Prague.\nLa tour de l’observatoire, en haut de la colline, est une réplique –en plus petit- de la tour Eiffel de Paris.\nAccès: Le funiculaire se prend à la station de tram Ujezd (lignes 12, 22, 23). On peut également accéder à la colline à partir du couvent de Strahov.\n\nSi vous avez une petite faim en redescendant, arrêtez vous à l\'excellent restaurant Nebozizek, à mi-hauteur sur la colline. La nourriture servie est excellente, et les prix plutôt raisonnables si on considère la vue extraordinaire sur la ville, qui est incluse dans le prix!','Petrin Hill','','inherit','open','open','','285-revision-3','','','2010-06-24 21:55:48','2010-06-24 20:55:48','',285,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/285-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1583,1,'2010-06-24 21:58:54','2010-06-24 20:58:54','Prague offers quantities of sites to visit. Apart from its famous castle, there is the Charles Bridge, the oldest and best known of the 14 bridges that cross the Vltava. This bridge is easily recognizable thanks to the 30 statues that overlook each of its pillars. It connects the historic Old Town and Mala Strana.\r\nYou should know that the bridge work is currently expected to last much longer, probably until 2020. This does not prevent access to the bridge but may however interfere with vision.\r\nAnother drawback, not least, is that it\'s very popular. At certain hours, you will not find only painters, musicians and vendors: it is almost impossible to move forward as it is crowded with tourists! And of course, who says tourists says pickpockets! Watch your wallet and your camera when you walk on the bridge ...\r\nTo learn more about the history of Charles Bridge, there is a museum open to the public since 2007 with exhibits. Admission is 6.50 euros.','Le Pont Charles','','inherit','open','open','','283-revision-3','','','2010-06-24 21:58:54','2010-06-24 20:58:54','',283,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/283-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1582,1,'2010-06-24 21:58:35','2010-06-24 20:58:35','Prague offers quantities of sites to visit. Apart from its famous castle, there is the Charles Bridge, the oldest and best known of the 14 bridges that cross the Vltava. This bridge is easily recognizable thanks to the 30 statues that overlook each of its pillars. It connects the historic Old Town and Mala Strana.\nYou should know that the bridge work is currently expected to last much longer, probably until 2020. This does not prevent access to the bridge but may however interfere with vision.\nAnother drawback, not least, is that it\'s very popular. At certain hours, you will not find only painters, musicians and vendors: it is almost impossible to move forward as it is crowded with tourists! And of course, who says tourists says pickpockets! Watch your wallet and your camera when you walk on the bridge ...\nTo learn more about the history of Charles Bridge, is a museum open to the public since 2007 with exhibits. Admission is 6.50 euros.Prague offre des quantités de sites à visiter. Hormis son célèbre château, il y a le pont Charles, le plus ancien et le plus connu des 14 ponts qui traversent la Vltava. Ce pont est facilement reconnaissable grâce aux 30 statues qui surplombent chacun de ses piliers. Il relie la vieille ville historique et Mala Strana.\nIl faut savoir que le pont est actuellement travaux qui devraient durer encore longtemps, probablement 2020. Cela n\'empêche pas l\'accès au pont mais peut bien sûr gêner la vue.\nAutre inconvénient, et non des moindres: il est très populaire. A certaines heures, vous n\'y trouverez pas que des peintres, des musiciens et des vendeurs: il est quasiment impossible d’avancer tant il est encombré de touristes! Et bien évidemment, qui dit touristes dit pickpockets! Attention à votre protefeuille et votre appareil photo lorsque vous marchez sur le pont...\nPour en savoir plus sur l\'histoire du pont Charles, un musée est ouvert au public depuis 2007 avec des expositions . Le prix d\'entrée est de 6,50 euros.\nAddress: Křižovnické náměstí 3, Prague 1.','Le Pont Charles','','inherit','open','open','','283-revision-2','','','2010-06-24 21:58:35','2010-06-24 20:58:35','',283,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/283-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1584,1,'2010-06-24 22:42:26','2010-06-24 21:42:26','The most important attraction inPrague  is the huge medieval castle, which dominates the Old Town. Reputed to be the largest castle with its 570 meters long and 130 meters wide, its construction dates from the 10th century.\nIts opening hours are impressive: access to the castle is permitted every day from 5am to midnight in summer and 6am to 11pm in winter, and historical monuments open from 9am to 6pm. Castle gardens open at 10 in the morning and closing hours vary by season. The walks around the castle and the entrance to the cathedral is free, but you\'ll have to pay to access the main monuments, which are worth seeing. For more information about this world heritage site see UNESCO\'s official website.\n\nAddress: 11908 Prague.\nThe easiest way to get to the castle is to take tram No. 22 to the station Pražský hrad, then turn left. In five minutes you reach the castle. You can also get off the tram at the station Pohořelec and down the hill to the castle, allowing you to add a nice walk to your visit.\nTwo subway stations are close: Malostranská and Hradčanská.','The Prague Castle','','inherit','open','open','','281-revision-2','','','2010-06-24 22:42:26','2010-06-24 21:42:26','',281,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/281-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1586,1,'2010-06-24 23:05:52','2010-06-24 22:05:52','To dance, a must is the Karlovy Lazny. Open for over 10 years, this landmark dance place is recognized as the largest nightclub in central Europe. Its five-stories building built in the 14th century, offer  5 clubs in one. Each floor has its own style of music.\r\nEntrance costs 120 crowns after 10PM (only 70 if you arrive before) and the club is open until the wee hours of the morning. For 1000 crowns per person, there is a bar-open section the serious drinkers will enjoy ...\r\nAddress: Novotného Lavka 5, Stare Mesto.','Karlovy Lazny','','inherit','open','open','','277-revision-4','','','2010-06-24 23:05:52','2010-06-24 22:05:52','',277,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/277-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1585,1,'2010-06-24 23:04:53','2010-06-24 22:04:53','To dance, a must is the Karlovy Lazny. Open for over 10 years, this landmark dance place is recognized as the largest nightclub in central Europe. Its five-stories building built in the 14th century, offer  5 clubs in one. Each floor has its own style of music.\nEntrance costs 120 crowns after 10PM (only 70 if you arrive before) and the club is open until the wee hours of the morning. For 1000 crowns per person, it is even a section bar \"all inclusive\", where the serious drinkers will delight ...\nAddress: Novotného Lavka 5, Stare MestoPour danser, un incontournable est le Karlovy Lazny. Ouvert depuis plus de 10 ans, ce haut-lieu de la danse lieu est reconnu comme la plus grande discothèque d\'Europe centrale. Ses cinq étages aménagés dans un bâtiment du 14ième siècle, offrent en quelque sorte 5 clubs en 1. Chaque étage a son propre style de musique\nL\'entrée coûte 120 couronnes après 22h (c\'est 70 seulement si vous arrivez avant) et le club est ouvert jusqu\'aux petites heures du matin. Pour 1000 couronnes par personne, il y a même une section bar \"tout-inclus\", où les sérieux buveurs trouveront leur bonheur...\nAdresse: Novotného lávka 5, Staré Mesto','Karlovy Lazny','','inherit','open','open','','277-revision-3','','','2010-06-24 23:04:53','2010-06-24 22:04:53','',277,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/277-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1588,1,'2010-06-24 23:09:31','2010-06-24 22:09:31','Located in the historic center, near the central square, U Vejvodů, both bar and restaurant on two floors, offers traditional Czech dishes with good local beer, but also international beer. The lower level of the establishment, in the restaurant, features groups of Czech folk music. The style is young and trendy on the main level, and the bar is constantly filled, with locals as well as  tourists.\r\nBe cautious, however: check your bill, because many visitors have reported mistakes...\r\nAddress: Jilská 4, Prague 1. The nearest subway station is Národní třída, the bar is 100m away.','U Vejvodů','','inherit','open','open','','275-revision-5','','','2010-06-24 23:09:31','2010-06-24 22:09:31','',275,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/275-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1587,1,'2010-06-24 23:08:45','2010-06-24 22:08:45','Located in the historic center, near the central square, U Vejvodů, both bar and restaurant on two floors, offers traditional Czech dishes with good local beer, but also international beer. The lower level of the establishment, in the restaurant, features groups of Czech folk music. The style is young and trendy on the main level, and the bar is constantly filled, as well as local tourists.\nA caution, however: check your bill, because many visitors have reported errors ...\nAddress: Ji