to the Guinness, the world famous local beer, it is the Guinness Storehouse.\r\nIn this old building from the early 20th century where the Guinness was once brewed you learn everything about the production of this beer, and can buy some souvenirs, posters, postcards, etc.. It will also show you how to serve a pint of Guinness in the rules of art, and you can even drink it! The panoramic view of Dublin from the Gravity Bar alone is  worth a visit.\r\nTo save 10% of entry price and avoid the line-ups, please book online!\r\nThe Guinness Storehouse is open daily from 9.30 am to 5 pm. In summer, during the months of July and August, it remains open until 7 pm.\r\nIt is located in the brewery at St. James\'s Gate, that can easily be reached by foot, bus or tram. For those who come by car, free parking is available.','Guiness Storehouse','','inherit','open','open','','129-revision-5','','','2010-06-25 23:29:27','2010-06-25 22:29:27','',129,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/129-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1629,1,'2010-06-25 23:28:29','2010-06-25 22:28:29','The main attraction in Dublin is obviously related to the Guinness, the world famous local beer, it is the Guinness Storehouse.\nIn this old building from the early 20th century where the Guinness was once brewed you learn everything about the production of this beer, and can buy some souvenirs, posters, postcards, etc.. It will also show you how to serve a pint of Guinness in the rules of art, and you can even drink it! The panoramic view of Dublin from the Gravity Bar is alone worth a visit.\nTo save 10% of entry price and avoid the queues, please book online!\nThe Guinness Storehouse is opened daily from 9.30 am to 17h. In summer, during the months of July and August, it remains open until 19h.\nIt is located in the brewery at St. James\'s Gate, one can easily reach by foot, bus or tram. For those who come by car, free parking is available.\n\nL’attraction principale à Dublin est bien évidemment liée à la Guinness, bière locale mondialement connue, il s’agit de la Guinness Storehouse.\nDans ce vieux bâtiment du début du 20ème siècle où la Guinness était fermentée autrefois, vous apprendrez tout sur la fabrication de cette bière, et pourrez acheter quelques souvenirs, affiches, cartes postales, etc. On vous y montrera aussi comment servir une pinte de Guinness dans les règles de l’art, et vous pourrez même la boire! La vue panoramique sur Dublin depuis le Gravity Bar vaut à elle seule une visite.\nPour économiser 10% du prix d’entrée et éviter de faire la queue, pensez à réserver en ligne!\nLa Guinness Storehouse est ouverte tous les jours de 9h30 à 17h. En été, durant les mois de juillet et août,  elle reste ouverte jusqu\'à 19h.\nElle se trouve dans la brasserie de Saint-James\'s Gate, on peut s\'y rendre très facilement à pied, en bus ou en tram. Pour ceux qui s\'y rendent en voiture, un parking gratuit est offert.','Guiness Storehouse','','inherit','open','open','','129-revision-4','','','2010-06-25 23:28:29','2010-06-25 22:28:29','',129,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/129-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1640,1,'2010-06-24 23:30:04','2010-06-24 22:30:04','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1300\" title=\"amsterdam_melkweg\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/amsterdam_melkweg-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Melkweg Amwsterdam\" width=\"300\" height=\"201\" />A very popular place in Amsterdam, whose name means \"Milky Way\". The Melkweg is located downtown, near the Leidseplein.\r\n\r\nIt is an old brick warehouse which was converted in a cultural center where are featured not only many rock and pop concerts, but also photo exhibits, film screenings, dance performances and all kinds of cultural activities. Big names as well as local groups perform there.\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<div id=\"tts_button\" title=\"Écouter la traduction\"><object id=\"tts_flash\" classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" codebase=