ong>youth hostels</strong>. The booklet also contains a map of the museum to further facilitate self guided tours.\n\nIf you are passionate about art and especially Van Gogh, know that the Van Gogh Museum has a specialized library containing over 24,000 books on Van Gogh and other artists of the nineteenth century.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nThe Van Gogh Museum is located on the Museumplein. The entrance is at number 7 at the Paulus Potterstraat. The museum is easily accessible by public transportation (tram lines 2, 3, 5 and 12 and buses 170, 171 and 172) which may be very close to your <strong>youth hostel</strong>.\nThe museum is open daily from 10AM to 6PM, however, on Fridays it closes later at 10Pm.\nAdmission is 14 euros but is free for those under 18. Unfortunately, there is no student discount.','Van Gogh museum in Amsterdam','The number one paid attraction in Amsterdam is the Van Gogh Museum which is dedicated to the life and works of the prolific painter. The museum opened in 1973 and received a wing for modern architecture in 1999. It is visited by approximately 1.5 million people each year. Located near many youth hostels it is  popular among backpackers. ','inherit','open','open','','1295-autosave','','','2010-09-09 23:31:24','2010-09-09 22:31:24','',1295,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1295-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1646,1,'2010-06-24 15:41:08','2010-06-24 14:41:08','<p><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1288\" title=\"amsterdamuseum\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/amsterdamuseum-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Musée van Gogh\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />The number one paid attraction of Amsterdam is the Van Gogh Museum, dedicated to the life and work of the prolific painter. Opened in 1973, and with a wing of modern architecture since 1999, it is visited by approximately 1.5 million visitors each year.<br />\r\nAt this museum, one can see more paintings of the famous painter than anywhere in the world. Paintings like The Sunflowers or self-portrait of the artist are part of the permanent collection.</p>\r\n<p>Guided tours are not offered by the Museum but can be booked with an outside guide. If you prefer to visit the museum by yourself, at least get the booklet about the life of Van Gogh. Available in French at the information desk, it also contains a map of the museum.</p>\r\n<p>And if you are passionate about art and especially Van Gogh, know that the Van Gogh Museum has a specialized library with over 24,000 books on Van Gogh and other artists of the nineteenth century.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Directions</strong><br />\r\nThe Van Gogh Museum is located on the Museumplein. The entrance is at number 7 at the Paulus Potterstraat. The museum is easily accessible by public transportation (tram lines 2, 3, 5 and 12 and buses 170, 171 and 172).<br />\r\nIt is open daily from 10 to 18 and closes later on Friday, at 22h.<br />\r\nAdmission is 14 euros, but is free for those under 18. Unfortunately there is no student discount.</p>\r\n','Van Gogh museum in Amsterdam','L’attraction payante numéro un d’Amsterdam est le Musée Van Gogh, dédié à la vie et l’oeuvre du peintre prolifique. Ouvert en 1973, et doté d’une aile à l’architecture moderne depuis 1999, il est visité par environ 1.5 millions de visiteurs chaque année.','inherit','open','open','','1295-revision-5','','','2010-06-24 15:41:08','2010-06-24 14:41:08','',1295,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1295-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1649,1,'2010-06-24 15:48:48','2010-06-24 14:48:48','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1250\" title=\"dublinmaritime\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/dublinmaritime-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Festival maritime à Dublin\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nIf you spend a weekend in Dublin in early June, do not miss the maritime festival, organized by the Dublin Docklands Authority. In a lively area where new attractions keep appearing, this festival celebrates 