he transportation system, one of the most efficient and modern in Europe, which is in constant development. The tram goes mainly to the eastern part of the city. If time permits, rent bikes because the city is rather flat and offers \"highly developed bike paths that can be used safely. If necessary, you are allowed to carry your bike on the train.\r\n\r\nTo go from the eastern to the western part of the city and vice versa, the buses 100 and 200 are very practical.\r\n\r\nThe different transport systems allow the use of a single ticket that costs depending on the number of zones you travel. You can also buy a day pass that allows unlimited travel.\r\n\r\nAnd of course, Berlin is bisected by the River Spree where you may travel by boat to combine business activities with pleasure. All kinds of excursions are possible.\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 206px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow: hidden;\">\r\n\r\nBerlin is huge, much bigger than Paris! In north-eastern Germany,  Berlin has 12 administrative districts, each with their own style that  offers kind of several \"downtowns\" in Berlin.\r\n\r\nOn the last count, Berlin had 3.5 million inhabitants and a total of 5  million people originating from 180 countries.\r\n\r\nThe language spoken is German (English is also frequently spoken),  and the currency used is the euro.\r\n\r\n</div>','Berlin','Berlin is huge, much bigger than Paris! In north-eastern Germany, Berlin has 12 administrative districts, each with their own style that offers kind of several \"downtowns\" in Berlin.\r\n\r\nOn the last count, Berlin had 3.5 million inhabitants and a total of 5 million people originating from 180 countries.\r\n\r\nThe language spoken is German (English is also frequently spoken), and the currency used is the euro.','inherit','open','open','','323-revision-17','','','2010-07-06 05:54:02','2010-07-06 04:54:02','',323,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/323-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1739,1,'2010-07-05 19:04:39','2010-07-05 18:04:39','<a href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/?attachment_id=1835\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1835\" title=\"Los-angeles\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/Los-angeles2-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>What to say about Los Angeles... the City of Angels, commonly known as LA? First, you must know that this California city, with its population of more than 10 million inhabitants, is the second largest city in the United States. The main language is English and the currency is the U.S. dollar. The city has a pleasant climate throughout the year. In summer the average temperature is 24°C and in winter it is around 10°C. It rarely rains there, but rainfalls are usually violent. Despite the fact that the climate may seem ideal, Los Angeles is too often affected by smog in summer, which can cause respiratory problems in people who are sensitive to it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you arrive in Los Angeles by air, it is important to note that the Airport (Los Angeles International Airport - LAX) is located about 20 km from downtown. You will need to take a taxi or rent a car to get to your hostel. Since Los Angeles is a very big city, it is impossible to visit it by foot. There is a subway system which can be useful but it is still underdeveloped (only 5 lines), and a network of buses which is fairly slow. Since the public transport system is not very effective, it is highly recommended that you rent a vehicle for the duration of your stay so you can move between your hotel and the various points of interest. Some hostels offer shuttle services, don\'t hesitate to ask. For security issues, because unfortunately the City of Angels is not only inhabited by angels, do not leave anything in your rental car and do not go downtown after dusk.\r\n\r\n<strong>Lodging</strong>\r\n\r\nYou\'ll find lots of hostels at affordable prices in different neighborhoods of Los Angeles; you\'ll be spoiled for choice between different establishments. Be sure to choose your hostel to suit your tastes and needs, which will help make your stay comfortable and why not ... unforgettable! LA is a cosmopolitan city (more than 140 nationalities are represented) so you can enjoy all-American food or a more exotic cuisine to suit your taste and your mood. The choice of restaurants is vast; therefore, wherever you are you will always find something good to eat to satisfy a craving!','Los Angeles','Who says Los Angeles also says Hollywood! This neighborhood has welcomed its first studio in 1911 and has continued to expand to become the world capital of cinema it is still today. Discover Los Angeles, symbol of the \"amirecan dream\"!','publish','open','open','','youth-hostel-los-angeles','','','2013-03-03 13:47:00','2013-03-03 12:47:00','',42,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/?page_id=1739',0,'page','',0),(1740,1,'2010-07-05 18:54:56','2010-07-05 17:54:56','What to say about Los Angeles, the City of Angels, commonly known as LA? First, you must know that this California city, with its population of more than 10 million inhabitants, is the second largest city in the United States. The main language is English and the currency is the U.S. dollar. The city has a pleasant climate throughout the year. In summer the average temperature is 24°C and in winter it is around 10°C. It rarely rains there, but rainfalls are usually violent. Despite the fact that the climate may seem ideal, Los Angeles is too often affected by smog in summer, which can cause respiratory problems in people who are sensitive to it.\n\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\n\nIf you arrive in Los Angeles by air, it is important to note that the Airport (Los Angeles International Airport - LAX) is located about 20 km from downtown. You will need to take a taxi or rent a car to get to your hostel. Since Los Angeles is a very big city, it is impossible to visit it by