,'2010-07-06 06:43:20','2010-07-06 05:43:20','What to say about Los Angeles, the City of Angels, commonly known as LA? First, you must know that this California city, with its population of more than 10 million inhabitants, is the second largest city in the United States. The main language is English and the currency is the U.S. dollar. The city has a pleasant climate throughout the year. In summer the average temperature is 24°C and in winter it is around 10°C. It rarely rains there, but rainfalls are usually violent. Despite the fact that the climate may seem ideal, Los Angeles is too often affected by smog in summer, which can cause respiratory problems in people who are sensitive to it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you arrive in Los Angeles by air, it is important to note that the Airport (Los Angeles International Airport - LAX) is located about 20 km from downtown. You will need to take a taxi or rent a car to get to your hostel. Since Los Angeles is a very big city, it is impossible to visit it by foot. There is a subway system which can be useful but it is still underdeveloped (only 5 lines), and a network of buses which is fairly slow. Since the public transport system is not very effective, it is highly recommended that you rent a vehicle for the duration of your stay so you can move between your hotel and the various points of interest. Some hostels offer shuttle services, don\'t hesitate to ask. For security issues, because unfortunately the City of Angels is not only inhabited by angels, do not leave anything in your rental car and do not go downtown after dusk.\r\n\r\n<strong>Lodging</strong>\r\n\r\nYou\'ll find lots of hostels at affordable prices in different neighborhoods of Los Angeles; you\'ll be spoiled for choice between different establishments. Be sure to choose your hostel to suit your tastes and needs, which will help make your stay comfortable and why not ... unforgettable! LA is a cosmopolitan city (more than 140 nationalities are represented) so you can enjoy all-American food or a more exotic cuisine to suit your taste and your mood. The choice of restaurants is vast; therefore, wherever you are you will always find something good to eat to satisfy a craving!','Los Angeles','Who says Los Angeles also says Hollywood! This neighborhood has welcomed its first studio in 1911 and has continued to expand to become the world capital of cinema it is still today. Discover Los Angeles, symbol of the \"amirecan dream\"!','inherit','open','open','','1739-revision-15','','','2010-07-06 06:43:20','2010-07-06 05:43:20','',1739,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1739-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1838,4,'2010-07-06 05:41:31','2010-07-06 04:41:31','Although located in a tourist area NoFeesHostels.com recommends Coctail, a restaurant-bar which is located near the Charles Bridge. Coctail offers entrees for about 150 crowns.\r\n\r\nAddress: Karlova 6, Stare Mesto.','Le Coctail','','inherit','open','open','','300-revision-5','','','2010-07-06 05:41:31','2010-07-06 04:41:31','',300,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/300-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1839,4,'2010-06-24 20:23:46','2010-06-24 19:23:46','Hostel located right between the Olympic Stadium and Old Montreal!','Qualitas Hostel Apartement ','','inherit','open','open','','506-revision-8','','','2010-06-24 20:23:46','2010-06-24 19:23:46','',506,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/506-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1840,4,'2010-07-06 07:50:18','2010-07-06 06:50:18','Hostel located right between the Olympic Stadium and Old Montreal!','Qualitas Youth Hostel Apartement ','','inherit','open','open','','506-revision-9','','','2010-07-06 07:50:18','2010-07-06 06:50:18','',506,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/506-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1841,4,'2010-06-26 00:42:43','2010-06-25 23:42:43','Best ratings in Barcelona for the  last 2 years!! BREAKFAST, LOCKERS, INTERNET, SHEETS, BLANKETS AND ACTIVITIES FOR FREE!!!!\r\n\r\nWe are all backpackers like you, inspired on our journeys, we dreamt about opening our own house to share the travelling experience with other people.\r\n\r\nIn Mambo Tango you will find a familiar, friendly and young atmosphere where you will find us the whole day.\r\n\r\nIf you are people who want to make new friends, have a beer, enjoy the hostel atmosphere, enjoy Barcelona,you are really welcome! Our success is based on the respect to others!!\r\n\r\nMambo Tango family is not a party hostel, is not a drunk hostel, is not a messy hostel, and is not an unrespectful hostel, and above all is not a hostel where people does not respect others sleeping in room. Mambo Tango is a respecful and peaceful hostel. If you want to book here please don\'t forget it.','Mambo Tango Hostel','Best ratings in Barcelona for the last 2 years!! BREAKFAST, LOCKERS, INTERNET, SHEETS, BLANKETS AND ACTIVITIES FOR FREE!!!!','inherit','open','open','','446-revision-11','','','2010-06-26 00:42:43','2010-06-25 23:42:43','',446,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/446-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1842,4,'2010-06-24 20:26:08','2010-06-24 19:26:08','Welcome to ALL STAR HOSTEL, a new hostel located near the subway station at Kilburn in North West London zone 2!','ALL STAR Hostel','','inherit','open','open','','502-revision-6','','','2010-06-24 20:26:08','2010-06-24 19:26:08','',502,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/502-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1843,4,'2010-07-06 07:54:03','2010-07-06 06:54:03','Welcome to ALL STAR HOSTEL, a new hostel located near the subway station at Kilburn in North West London zone 2!','ALL STAR Youth Hostel','','inherit','open','open','','502-revision-7','','','2010-07-06 07:54:03','2010-07-06 06:54:03','',502,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/502-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1844,4,'2010-07-06 05:49:40','2010-07-06 04:49:40','<img class=\"size-full wp-image-343 alignleft\" title=\"Plaza Real Barcelone\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/IMG_2602-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Plaza Real Barcelone\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" />\r\n\r\nSecond city of Spain, prosperous and vibrant, the capital of the province of Catalonia covers about 490 square kilometres with 1.5 million people. Located along the Mediterranean coast, it is a major Spanish center not only for its economic but also cultural and touristic boldness.\r\nThe two languages commonly spoken in Barcelona are the Castilian (Spanish) and Catalan. The signs and posters are written in Catalan, but if you talk to people in Spanish, they will respond in that language. The currency is the Euro.\r\n<h3>Arriving and moving around Barcelona</h3>\r\nWe move around in Barcelona by metro, bus or taxi. The most simple and practical means of transport is the subway, which lets visitors reach some outlying attractions such as Park Guell.\r\nInstead of buying individual tickets, if you intend to take the subway several times in the same day, it is more economical to purchase a tourist pass for several days. In addition, these cards are valid in buses as well as the subway. You can also buy the tickets by 10, which is cheaper than per unit.\r\nIn downtown, the Gothic Quarter is usually and easily visited on foot, as is Las Ramblas.  The climate of Barcelona will not force you to lock yourself too often to seek protection from the rain.','Barcelona','Second city of Spain, prosperous and vibrant, the capital of the province of Catalonia covers about 490 square kilometres with 1.5 million people. Located along the Mediterranean coast, it is a major Spanish center not only for its economic but also cultural and touristic boldness.\r\nThe two languages commonly spoken in Barcelona are the Castilian (Spanish) and Catalan. The signs and posters are written in Catalan, but if you talk to people in Spanish, they will respond in that language. The currency is the Euro.','inherit','open','open','','398-revision-23','','','2010-07-06 05:49:40','2010-07-06 04:49:40','',398,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/398-revision-23/',0,'revision','',0),(1845,4,'2010-07-06 06:11:53','2010-07-06 05:11:53','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1093\" title=\"Pont de la Tour à Londres\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/london1-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Londres, Tower Bridge\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nWho has not dreamed of setting foot in London, the capital of England, once in his life, even if it is only to have a closer look at the Big Ben? Greater London covers an area of approximately 1584 km2, where 7.2 million people live and enjoy the many activities offered.  London is the largest metropolis in Europe, the first global financial center, and the site of many cultural experiments. In addition, it will host the next Summer Olympics in 2012!\r\n\r\nEnglish is a must wherever you go, but you must know that nearly 300 languages are spoken in London, including Hindu, Chinese and Hebrew. Indeed, the city hosts since 1940 are immigrants from former colonies of the British Empire like the West Indies, India and Pakistan.\r\n\r\nDespite the fact that the UK is part of the European Union, they decided to keep the pound sterling as currency and not to adopt the Euro.\r\n\r\nFollow our guide to find some ideas where to go out and how to better organize your trip. And of course, do not forget to look for the best accommodation for your stay with <a href=\"http://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&amp;sl=fr&amp;tl=en&amp;prev=_t&amp;u=http://www.aubergesdejeunesse.com/wp-admin/auberges/recherche/England/London\">our reservation</a> system! We offer the best hosting plans, youth hostels, small hotels of charm in all areas of London.','London','Who has not dreamed of setting foot in London, the capital of England, once in his life, even if it is only to have a closer look at the Big Ben? Greater London covers an area of approximately 1584 km2, where 7.2 million people live and enjoy the many activities offered.  London is the largest metropolis in Europe, the first global financial center, and the site of many cultural experiments. In addition, it will host the next Summer Olympics in 2012!','inherit','open','open','','1085-revision-10','','','2010-07-06 06:11:53','2010-07-06 05:11:53','',1085,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1085-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1846,4,'2010-07-06 06:48:13','2010-07-06 05:48:13','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-525\" title=\"Paris\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/IMG_7002-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Le Louvre\" width=\"217\" height=\"162\" />\r\n\r\n\"Paris, queen of the world ...\" The international reputation of the capital of France is one of the most popular destinations in the world, for many reasons.\r\n\r\nParis covers over 500,000 km2 and is inhabited by more than 2 million people (almost 12 million including the surrounding suburbs).\r\n\r\nThey speak French, and the currency used is the Euro.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Arriving in Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nParis has two main airports, Orly and Charles de Gaulle, also known as Roissy. You can reach the center of Paris easily by bus. The Orlybus goes to Denfert-Rochereau and Roissybus serves the Opera metro station. From Orly, it is also possible to take the subway called Orlyval.\r\n\r\n<strong>In Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nParis is a great city, and to get from one point to another you\'ll probably need to use public transport: bus, metro, RER. The company that manages public transport in Paris is called the RATP.\r\n\r\nTaking the metro can be unpleasant during rush hour, but you may want to use it anyway to visit some of the beautiful stations. Do not miss the following stations: Abbesses, Arts et Metiers, Palais Royal and Pont Neuf.\r\n\r\nYou can also discover Paris by boat, along the Seine. Weather permitting, you should absolutely walk or bike too.  The bicycle leasing system with terminals throughout the city, the Vélib, is perfect.  If you plan to visit many areas of Paris in a few days, it is recommended to purchase the package offered by the RATP, the Paris Visite. This package is valid for 1, 2, 3 or 5 consecutive days, on zones 1 to 3 or 1 to 6, and costs between 9-50 euros depending on the plan you choose. There are other options to suit all needs, please inquire at the RATP desk upon arrival for maximum savings. The Paris Metro is very developed and offers you access to all points of interest fairly quickly.\r\n\r\nUnless you have a good knowledge of Paris, or an effective co-pilot, do not do your travel by car.\r\n\r\n<strong>Accommodation in Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nFrom a simple hostel to five star hotels, through bed &amp; breakfast, there\'s something for every taste and every budget in Paris.\r\nYou will find on our site (in the right menu) a selection of hostels and other types of housing in the most recommended neighbourhoods of Paris. A single click will allow you to make a reservation!\r\n\r\nTo see the complete list of hostels and make your reservation, <a href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/france/paris\">go to our list .</a>','Paris','\"Paris, queen of the world ...\" The international reputation of the capital of France is one of the most popular destinations in the world, for many reasons.\r\n\r\nParis covers over 500,000 km2 and is inhabited by more than 2 million people (almost 12 million including the surrounding suburbs).\r\n\r\nThey speak French, and the currency used is the Euro.','inherit','open','open','','524-revision-24','','','2010-07-06 06:48:13','2010-07-06 05:48:13','',524,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/524-revision-24/',0,'revision','',0),(1847,4,'2010-07-06 07:03:08','2010-07-06 06:03:08','The capital of the Czech Republic is also the largest city in this country.  It covers an area of 496 km2 with more than 1.2 million residents, which represents nearly 1/8th of the total population.\r\n\r\nThe country\'s official language is Czech, a Slavic language similar to Polish and Slovak. Ability to speak German and English off course can be useful, but you\'ll probably have few opportunities to speak French.\r\n\r\nThe official currency is the Czech Crown, and even if the euro is accepted in tourist sites and restaurants, it is not recommended to use because the exchange rate is not favourable.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\nPrague has two main systems of transport, tram and metro. There are only three subway lines, which do not cover all areas of the city, but are fast and convenient. Moreover, the tram links all sites of interest and is a great way to visit Prague.\r\n\r\nIn practical terms, if you intend to move primarily using public transportation, buy a travel ticket valid for 24 hours at a reasonable cost (a hundred crowns) which is usable in all modes of transportation. There are other passes for longer stays: 3, 5 or 7 days.\r\n\r\nIt is not necessary to use public transportation since most of the sites and attractions are easily accessible on foot, but it saves time. For example, you can climb the steps to the Castle from the old town and down the tram.\r\n\r\nTry to avoid taking a taxi because problems are common.  Taxi drivers do not always start their taximeter at the start of the trip, and scams are commonplace.\r\n\r\nIf time permits, biking in Prague is also a good idea.  Avoid driving a car even if the traffic is low, it\'s so easy to walk around town...','Prague','The capital of the Czech Republic is also the largest city in this country.  It covers an area of 496 km2 with more than 1.2 million residents, which represents nearly 1/8th of the total population.\r\n\r\nThe country\'s official language is Czech, a Slavic language similar to Polish and Slovak. Ability to speak German and English off course can be useful, but you\'ll probably have few opportunities to speak French.\r\n\r\nThe official currency is the Czech Crown, and even if the euro is accepted in tourist sites and restaurants, it is not recommended to use because the exchange rate is not favourable.','inherit','open','open','','195-revision-21','','','2010-07-06 07:03:08','2010-07-06 06:03:08','',195,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/195-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1848,1,'2010-07-14 00:20:15','2010-07-13 23:20:15','[caption id=\"attachment_1876\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"225\" caption=\"Quebec City by Sue Byford\"]<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-1876\" href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/youth-hostel-destinations/quebec-city/quebec-automne2/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1876\" title=\"Quebec automne2\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/Quebec-automne2-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Quebec City by Sue Byford\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nCapital of the Canadian province that bears his name, Quebec is a city whose charm is matched only by its beautiful landscape. Taking its name from the Algonquin language, Quebec means \"where the river narrows\", which of course refers to the majestic St. Lawrence River on whose banks the city is built.\r\n\r\nThis beautiful city, which was founded in 1608 by Samuel de Champlain, brings us back into the eventful past of this colony which was initially called \"Nouvelle-France\" and which remains today the cradle of the French language in North America. The only walled city north of Mexico, Quebec City will delight you with its historic buildings, some of which have been converted into hostels, as well as its vast green spaces.\r\n\r\nQuebec City has about 508,000 inhabitants spread over six districts. The main language is French and currency is the Canadian dollar. Regarding gastronomy, one can find restaurants for all tastes, which are usually open all day and into the evening. Whether you want to enjoy a 5-course meal or just have a quick lunch, you will find a place that easily match your tastes and your budget. Some hostels even offer meals, ask your hosts!\r\n\r\nQuebec City is often referred to as a \"village\". However, it is anyway large enough that you will need a mean of transportation to get from one place to another.\r\n\r\nQuebec City  has a very effective network of public transport (Réseau de Transport de la Capitale). More than 500 buses are serving the area, making it the second largest network of public transport in the province. For those who prefer taking a cab, several companies are available who will gladly take you directly to the door of your hostel and take you to your destination.\r\n\r\nIt is also relatively easy to travel by car in Quebec City. The road signs are clear and traffic jams are relatively rare.','Quebec City','Québec, a beautiful city which was founded in 1608 by Samuel de Champlain, brings us back into the eventful past of this colony which was initially called \"Nouvelle-France\" and which remains today the cradle of the French language in North America.','publish','open','open','','quebec-city','','','2013-03-03 13:52:32','2013-03-03 12:52:32','',42,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/?page_id=1848',0,'page','',0),(1849,1,'2010-07-14 00:17:52','2010-07-13 23:17:52','Capital of the Canadian province that bears his name, Quebec is a city whose charm is matched only by its beautiful landscape. Taking its name from the Algonquin language, Quebec means \"where the river narrows\", which of course refers to the majestic St. Lawrence River on whose banks the city is built.\n\nThis beautiful city, which was founded in 1608 by Samuel de Champlain, brings us back into the eventful past of this colony which was initially called \"Nouvelle-France\" and which remains today the cradle of the French language in North America. The only walled city north of Mexico, Quebec City will delight you with its historic buildings, some of which have been converted into hostels, as well as its vast green spaces.\n\nQuebec City has about 508,000 inhabitants spread over six districts. The main language is French and currency is the Canadian