oors, offers traditional Czech dishes with good local beer, but also international beer. The lower level of the establishment, in the restaurant, features groups of Czech folk music. The style is young and trendy on the main level, and the bar is constantly filled, with locals as well as  tourists.\r\nBe cautious, however: check your bill, because many visitors have reported mistakes...\r\nAddress: Jilská 4, Prague 1. The nearest subway station is Národní třída, the bar is 100m away.','U Vejvodů','','inherit','open','open','','275-revision-7','','','2010-06-26 00:56:44','2010-06-25 23:56:44','',275,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/275-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1975,1,'2010-09-15 04:36:33','2010-09-15 03:36:33','Located in the historic center, near the central square, U Vejvodů, both bar and restaurant on two floors, offers traditional Czech dishes with good local beer, but also international beer. The lower level of the establishment, in the restaurant, features groups of Czech folk music. The style is young and trendy on the main level, and the bar is constantly filled, with locals as well as  tourists.\nBe cautious, however: check your bill, because many visitors have reported mistakes...\nAddress: Jilská 4, Prague 1. The nearest subway station is Národní třída. The bar is 100m away.','U Vejvodů','','inherit','open','open','','275-autosave','','','2010-09-15 04:36:33','2010-09-15 03:36:33','',275,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/275-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1976,1,'2010-07-06 07:40:11','2010-07-06 06:40:11','<a href=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/?attachment_id=1835\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1835\" title=\"Los-angeles\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/Los-angeles2-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>What to say about Los Angeles, the City of Angels, commonly known as LA? First, you must know that this California city, with its population of more than 10 million inhabitants, is the second largest city in the United States. The main language is English and the currency is the U.S. dollar. The city has a pleasant climate throughout the year. In summer the average temperature is 24°C and in winter it is around 10°C. It rarely rains there, but rainfalls are usually violent. Despite the fact that the climate may seem ideal, Los Angeles is too often affected by smog in summer, which can cause respiratory problems in people who are sensitive to it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you arrive in Los Angeles by air, it is important to note that the Airport (Los Angeles International Airport - LAX) is located about 20 km from downtown. You will need to take a taxi or rent a car to get to your hostel. Since Los Angeles is a very big city, it is impossible to visit it by foot. There is a subway system which can be useful but it is still underdeveloped (only 5 lines), and a network of buses which is fairly slow. Since the public transport system is not very effective, it is highly recommended that you rent a vehicle for the duration of your stay so you can move between your hotel and the various points of interest. Some hostels offer shuttle services, don\'t hesitate to ask. For security issues, because unfortunately the City of Angels is not only inhabited by angels, do not leave anything in your rental car and do not go downtown after dusk.\r\n\r\n<strong>Lodging</strong>\r\n\r\nYou\'ll find lots of hostels at affordable prices in different neighborhoods of Los Angeles; you\'ll be spoiled for choice between different establishments. Be sure to choose your hostel to suit your tastes and needs, which will help make your stay comfortable and why not ... unforgettable! LA is a cosmopolitan city (more than 140 nationalities are represented) so you can enjoy all-American food or a more exotic cuisine to suit your taste and your mood. The choice of restaurants is vast; therefore, wherever you are you will always find something good to eat to satisfy a craving!','Los Angeles','Who says Los Angeles also says Hollywood! This neighborhood has welcomed its first studio in 1911 and has continued to expand to become the world capital of cinema it is still today. Discover Los Angeles, symbol of the \"amirecan dream\"!','inherit','open','open','','1739-revision-16','','','2010-07-06 07:40:11','2010-07-06 06:40:11','',1739,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1739-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1979,1,'2010-09-15 05:54:35','2010-09-15 04:54:35','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-525\" title=\"Paris\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/IMG_7002-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Le Louvre\" width=\"217\" height=\"162\" />\r\n\r\n\"Paris, queen of the world ...\" The international reputation of the capital of France is one of the most popular destinations in the world, for many reasons.\r\n\r\nParis covers over 500,000 km2 and is inhabited by more than 2 million people (almost 12 million including the surrounding suburbs).\r\n\r\nThey speak French, and the currency used is the Euro.\r\n\r\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Arriving in Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nParis has two main airports, Orly and Charles de Gaulle, also known as Roissy. You can reach the center of Paris easily by bus. The Orlybus goes to Denfert-Rochereau and Roissybus serves the Opera metro station. From Orly, it is also possible to take the subway called Orlyval.\r\n\r\n<strong>In Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nParis is a great city, and to get from one point to another you\'ll probably need to use public transport: bus, metro, RER. The company that manages public transport in Paris is called the RATP.\r\n\r\nTaking the metro can be unpleasant during rush hour, but you may want to use it anyway to visit some of the beautiful stations. Do not miss the following stations: Abbesses, Arts et Metiers, Palais Royal and Pont Neuf.\r\n\r\nYou can also discover Paris by boat, along the Seine. Weather permitting, you should absolutely walk or bike too.  The bicycle leasing system with terminals throughout the city, the Vélib, is perfect.  If you plan to visit many areas of Paris in a few days, it is recommended to purchase the package offered by the RATP, the Paris Visite. This package is valid for 1, 2, 3 or 5 consecutive days, on zones 1 to 3 or 1 to 6, and costs between 9-50 euros depending on the plan you choose. There are other options to suit all needs, please inquire at the RATP desk upon arrival for maximum savings. The Paris Metro is very developed and offers you access to all points of interest fairly quickly.\r\n\r\nUnless you have a good knowledge of Paris, or an effective co-pilot, do not do your travel by car.\r\n\r\n<strong>Accommodation in Paris</strong>\r\n\r\nFrom a simple hostel to five star hotels, through bed &amp; breakfast, there\'s something for every taste and every budget in Paris.\r\nYou will find on our site (in the right menu) a selection of hostels and other types of housing in the most recommended neighbourhoods of Paris. A single click will allow you to make a reservation!\r\n\r\nTo see the complete list of hostels and make your reservation, go to our list .','Paris','\"Paris, queen of the world ...\" The international reputation of the capital of France is one of the most popular destinations in the world, for many reasons.\r\n\r\nParis covers over 500,000 km2 and is inhabited by more than 2 million people (almost 12 million including the surrounding suburbs).\r\n\r\nThey speak French, and the currency used is the Euro.','inherit','open','open','','524-revision-28','','','2010-09-15 05:54:35','2010-09-15 04:54:35','',524,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/524-revision-28/',0,'revision','',0),(1980,1,'2010-07-15 00:17:56','2010-07-14 23:17:56','<img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/wp-content/uploads/Vieux-Québec.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"283\" height=\"213\" />Whether you are fond of open spaces, shopping or winter sports, you\'ll find your happiness in Quebec City. Petit-Champlain\'s quarter is full of charming little shops and places to visit. Indulge yourself with a tour of The Funiculaire, which connects the Petit-Champlain\'s quarter (Basse-Ville) to the Terrasse Dufferin (Haute-Ville), where you get an incredible view of the surrounding landscape. It is in the historic district of Vieux-Québec that \"Les Fêtes de la Nouvelle-France\" have been taking place during summer for many years now. This festive event will take you back into the past for a few days, nearly 400 years ago, when the Nouvelle-France was still a French colony.\r\n\r\nEach summer is also held Le Festival d\'été de Québec, which is defined as \"the largest outdoor arts festival in Canada.\" For ten days, the shows follow one another in the streets and on indoor and outdoor stages. In a few words, this is the great celebration of music!\r\n\r\nIf you have the chance to see Le Moulin à Images, do not hesitate and go for it! This masterpiece is the largest sound and images production that you will be given to see. Projected on the grain silos of the Vieux Port de Québec (a screen of more than 1800 feet long by 90 high!), pictures and movies relate the 400 year history of the city in 50 minutes. An amazing work of art!\r\n\r\nIf you travel during winter, come to attend the renowned Carnaval de Québec. Take your family to watch the parades, have a look at the Ice Palace, greet Bonhomme and taste the \"Caribou\"! Dress warmly, however, since the temperature can easily drop to -30 ° C during winter...  nothing better than enjoying a hot chocolate when you return to your hostel!\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Going out in Quebec City\r\n</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFor nightlife lovers, Quebec City has several establishments, from small neighborhood bars to nightclubs, music clubs, pubs and bistros. Most bars close at 3:00 AM on weekends.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re fond of culture, you will not be disappointed because Quebec City has several theaters and concert halls presenting diversified and quality shows.\r\n\r\nShopping addict, you will be served! There are several shopping centers in Quebec City, including Les Galeries de la Capitale, which houses an indoor amusement center complete with a carousel, a Ferris wheel and even a roller coaster!','Youth Hostel - Quebec City Attractions','','inherit','open','open','','1851-revision-5','','','2010-07-15 00:17:56','2010-07-14 23:17:56','',1851,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1851-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1981,1,'2010-07-06 06:59:29','2010-07-06 05:59:29','If you only spend a few days in Paris, you\'ll probably be a little frustrated if you don’t get to do all the things there are to be done. Paris has so much to offer in terms of output that it is difficult to make a choice!  Nightlife in Paris can cost dearly, not only because of the temptations that are so numerous, but also because the costs are relatively high. For example, on average, a beer will cost € 5-6. And of course, any drink will cost you much more if you sit at a sidewalk cafe near the monuments of Paris. Still, it\'s a moment that you may not want to miss, like having a drink at the legendary Café de Flore thinking of the great philosophers...\r\n\r\nAll districts have their own set of bars, but the more lively events are in Paris, around the Place de la Bastille, Latin Quarter and Montmartre. Rue Etienne Marcel near Les Halles has lots of nice little bars and bistros, not to mention the trendy boutiques, it\'s worth a stroll.\r\n\r\nOf course, if you do not drink, Paris is full of activities for the evening! Seeing the Eiffel Tower lights shine is one. Every night after 9 am, every hour, the Eiffel Tower lights up for 10 minutes to delight many passers-by who stop to look before continuing on their path.\r\n\r\nWatch the other monuments of the city light up, walk along the Seine, through one of the many bridges at sunset, walk along the Canal St Martin ... Paris at night is very romantic. And if you like dancing, be it salsa or tango, do not forget to go on the Quai St. Bernard, where dances are held throughout the summer, weather permitting, outdoors.\r\n\r\n<strong>Eat in Paris</strong>\r\nThe French cuisine is world renowned, and hence you will find in Paris a wonderful selection of restaurants ranging from simple to chic. Between the two, you will find many small cafes of very good quality for a reasonable price, but it is clear that eating in Paris costs on average more expensive than in other cities in France. Stay away from areas of great monuments to avoid the blow!\r\nFor smaller budgets, it is also possible to buy sandwiches, quiches and other snacks in bakeries, and eating on a bench in one of the many beautiful city parks.','Youth Hostel - Nightlife in Paris','','inherit','open','open','','1083-revision-10','','','2010-07-06 06:59:29','2010-07-06 05:59:29','',1083,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/1083-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1982,4,'2010-09-14 07:47:57','2010-09-14 06:47:57','<div>\r\n\r\nIntroducing Metropol NYC, New York\'s newest and best boutique <strong>y</strong><strong>outh hostel</strong>!\r\n\r\nWe know how it is: picking the right <strong>youth hostel</strong> for your visit to New York is critical. It\'s the first step in ensuring you enjoy your stay in the city.\r\n\r\nWell, rest easy: we created Metropol with a belief that lower rates shouldn\'t mean lower standards. We\'ve worked hard to create an environment that makes you feel right at home, and helps you make the most of your time here. So say goodbye to filthy dorms and cold showers, and say hello to Metropol!\r\n\r\n</div>','Metropole Youth Hostel','','inherit','open','open','','510-revision-17','','','2010-09-14 07:47:57','2010-09-14 06:47:57','',510,'http://www.nofeeshostels.com/info/510-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(2004,4,'2010-09-17 17:35:35','2010-09-17 16:35:35','Hosteling International\'s San Francisco C