e and independent but really I just never want to miss an opportunity to make a new friend. I jump at the chance to share my small amount of wisdom and experience with everyone I meet and am always looking for the next big adventure. For me, travel is more than a passion or a past-time but a way of life.\r\n\r\nAs a traveller I know that money can be tight. In order to stretch my dollar the furthest and have the most enjoyable travel experience I prefer to hostel rather than hustle. I have joined with hostels.com to share all the best-kept secrets on hostelling abroad. I’ve always been choosy about the hostels I stay in as I expect to maintain my high standards. I may be a snail but that doesn’t mean I can’t travel in style! Travelling in style to me means more than simply expecting the highest standards in cleanliness and service but also entails living in an affordable, sustainable and eco-friendly manner. I make certain that through all my travels I respect the environmental impact that my actions may cause and hope that you will too. We all have a role to play in ensuring that hostelling as a means of travel remains a sustainable option for future generations.\r\n\r\nLife is meant to be an adventure and travelling around the globe provides some of the best adventures imaginable. I am always on the move and never pass up the chance to party. If you’re looking for something new and interesting to do in the months coming I suggest you take a trip with me and follow my adventures through hostels.com. I will be going everywhere from the hottest concerts, hippest festivals and of course, providing advice on all the best hostels in between. The world is full of inspirational people and breathtaking scenery now is your chance to be part of history in the making. Don’t miss your chance to be part of this adventure!\r\n\r\nHappy travels everybody!\r\n\r\nLeo','Leo the backpacker','I’d like to think that I leave a memory, a trace of myself wherever I’ve travelled. \r\nTrav